cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.Distributed, cs.SY, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with distributing sensor data through network nodes and proposes a solution based on network node virtualization. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the proposed solution involves distributed caching. 
- cs.Distributed (Distributed Computing) is another possible category as the paper deals with distributing data through a network of nodes. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper proposes a solution for improving the performance of a system that involves sensor data. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also a possible category as the paper proposes a solution that involves modularization and virtualization of network nodes, which are software engineering concepts.
